---
import SiteLayout from '@layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout title="Liri Text" variant="content">
  <div class="ribbon" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <article class="content-surface prose">
    <h1>Liri Text</h1>
    <p>
      Liri Text is a cross-platform, Material Design text editor, currently in
      <span class="chip">alpha</span> stage.
    </p>
    <p>
      It aims to be a minimal and simple editor with the features expected from
      a modern text editor.
    </p>

    <h2>Features</h2>
    <div class="image-grid">
      <section>
        <h3>Straightforward</h3>
        <img src="/images/apps/text/screen_start.png" alt="Liri Text start screen" />
        <p>Liri Text has a straightforward UI so you can focus on your task.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Solid</h3>
        <img src="/images/apps/text/screen_editing_process_01.png" alt="Liri Text editing a file" />
        <p>Basic editing features are built for code, configuration files, and prose.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
        <h3>Syntax Highlighting</h3>
        <img src="/images/apps/text/screen_highlighting_01.png" alt="Liri Text syntax highlighting" />
        <p>
          Syntax coloring supports a wide range of languages through
          <a href="https://developer.gnome.org/gtksourceview/stable/lang-reference.html">GtkSourceView language definitions</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <h2>Contribute</h2>
    <p>
      Contributions can include design, code, translations, bug reports, and
      testing.
    </p>

    <h3>Design</h3>
    <p>
      Mockups and sketches are valuable. Start with the
      <a href="https://github.com/lirios/text/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3A%22needs+design%22">GitHub issue list</a>.
    </p>

    <h3>Code</h3>
    <div class="image-grid">
      <img src="/images/apps/text/screen_qtcreator_dev_01.png" alt="Liri Text development in Qt Creator" />
      <div>
        <p>
          Liri Text is written using Qt, C++, and QML. QtQuick Controls 2 and
          <a href="https://github.com/lirios/fluid">Fluid</a> provide the
          Material Design interface.
        </p>
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/lirios/text</code></pre>
        <md-filled-tonal-button href="https://github.com/lirios/text">Fork on GitHub</md-filled-tonal-button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Translations</h3>
    <p>Help translate Liri Text into your language.</p>
    <md-filled-button href="/get-involved/">Get Involved</md-filled-button>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
